&lt;h3&gt;Who you are&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Metropolis is seeking a Director, Benefits to set strategy and own accountability for all company-wide benefit programs across our 20,000+ employees. In this role, you will manage plan funding, claims experience, and financial risk while moving fluidly between leader-ready strategy and the details of a complex claim, compliance filing, or stuck process. You are an energized, hands-on player-coach who thrives in a fast-paced, high-growth environment, biased toward action, and capable of leveraging technology, automation, and AI to scale our People Operations function. Partnering closely with Finance and leading a dedicated team of four, you will build structure, establish continuous compliance, and maintain a competitive edge in the labor market.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What you&#39;ll do&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set a company-wide benefits strategy with near- and long-term goals that keeps Metropolis competitive, designing new plans and modifying existing ones based on current and future trends&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify opportunities to leverage AI and automation to streamline benefits, leave, and PTO processes while reducing manual work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the annual Open Enrollment strategy and ensure benefits communications are accurate, clear, and compelling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee the strategy, administration, and compliant tracking of all leave and PTO programs across the 20,000+ population, including return-to-work coordination&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage leave vendor and TPA relationships while integrating leave and PTO data across HRIS, payroll, and benefit systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hold accountability for compliance with federal and state benefits and leave laws, including ERISA, HIPAA, COBRA, FMLA, ADA, and AC&lt;/li&gt;
