&lt;h3&gt;Who we are&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The real world is the next frontier, and at Metropolis, we are creating the artificial intelligence to make it responsive. We are pioneering the Recognition Economy — a future where mundane repetition disappears and being known unlocks access, comfort and belonging everywhere you go. From transforming parking into a seamless drive-in, drive-out experience for millions of Members to expanding our intelligence layer across retail and hospitality, we are building a world that feels instinctive and magical. The future isn’t coming; it’s here, and we need builders, innovators and problem solvers to help us create it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Who you are&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-path-to-node=&quot;3,0&quot;&gt;Metropolis is seeking a Manager, Corporate FP&amp;amp;A - Consolidation to lead the orchestration of our corporate reporting cycle and the compilation, validation, and communication of global financial results. You will own the &quot;last mile&quot; of finance, taking raw data from various business units and refining it into a clear, unified narrative for executive leadership. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-path-to-node=&quot;3,2&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;citation-34&quot;&gt;You are a process-oriented leader who ensures seamless hand-offs between accounting and FP&amp;amp;A to deliver accurate, consistent, and strategic reporting outputs.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What you&#39;ll do&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and manage the Corporate Reporting Calendar, coordinating timelines across global business units, accounting, and tax to ensure a synchronized close&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Standardize reporting templates and submission protocols to ensure one version of the truth across the enterprise&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the primary liaison between the Controllership and FP&amp;amp;A teams to reconcile management reporting with statutory filings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Aggregate inputs from multiple P&amp;amp;L owners into a consolidated corporate view, ensuring all intercompany eliminations and corporate adjustments are accurately reflected&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform high-level integrity checks on consolidated data to identify anomalies before results reach the CFO&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the Bridge analysis, explaining the drivers of variance between Actuals, Budgets, and prior Forecasts at an enterprise level&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the assembly of the Monthly Executive Reporting Package and Board of Directors presentations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Synthesize qualitative commentary from various departments into a concise summary of business performance, risks, and opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Investor Relations to provide data and context for earnings call preparation and external guidance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate the current reporting workflow to identify bottlenecks and implement lean finance practices to shorten the reporting cycle; define and document standard operating procedures (SOPs) for the consolidation process to ensure business continuity and scalability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What we&#39;re looking for&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of progressive experience in Corporate FP&amp;amp;A, with a heavy emphasis on multi-entity consolidation and management reporting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to manage complex, multi-stakeholder workflows under tight deadlines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take vast amounts of data and extract the most important takeaways for an executive audience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A &quot;perfectionist&quot; approach to data—ensuring that every total, sub-total, and footnote ties out perfectly across all decks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional written communication skills for drafting executive summaries and board-level commentary&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience leveraging AI tools to transform static workflows into responsive, high-output processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
